@REM LESSON 01
@REM What is a Coding Assistant?
@REM ------------------------------------------------------




@REM A coding assistant is an AI tool that helps you write and understand code.
@REM Claude Code is different from a regular chat interface —
@REM it runs in the terminal and has full access to your project.


@REM What Claude Code can do:
@REM   - read and write files in your project
@REM   - run bash commands and scripts
@REM   - understand the full project structure (not just the current file)
@REM   - integrate with Git and GitHub
@REM   - connect to external tools via MCP protocol
@REM   - be extended with custom hooks and automations


@REM The key difference from something like GitHub Copilot or ChatGPT:
@REM Claude Code is an AGENT — it can take multi-step actions on its own
@REM without needing confirmation at every single step.

@REM Instead of asking "how do I fix this bug?"
@REM you can say "fix the bug in src/auth.ts, run the tests, and commit the result"
@REM and Claude will actually do all of it.





@REM Where it runs:
@REM   - directly in your terminal (CLI)
@REM   - not a plugin, not a browser extension
@REM   - works with any editor or no editor at all